  "bodyHtml": "<h2><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">What is a Credit Request ?</span></h2>\n<p><br><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">A Credit Request is a way of sending money to the customer&#39;s virtual wallet via a Back Market Tool in the Back Office. From this virtual wallet, the customer can at any time transfer all or part of their virtual wallet to their personal bank account, free of charge.</span><br><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"> </span></p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Which cases can a Credit Request be made?</span></h2>\n<p><br><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">The Quality Charter details all the cases when Back Market Agent will proceed with a goodwill gesture. A goodwill gesture means any gesture to compensate the customers. It can refer to a partial refund or a credit request, or other advantages offered to the customer. </span></p>\n<h2><br><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>For sales </strong></span></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"> Back Market Agents follow strict guidelines on Credit Requests outlined in the section<strong> 3.6 Goodwill gestures.</strong> Credit Requests prevail over partial refund for: missing, incompatible, defective accessories (see paragraph 3.6.2), shipping delays (see paragraph 3.6.1), in case of a refund failed for an order paid with Paypal (see paragraph 3.5.5), missing IMEI/Serial Number (see paragraph 2.2) or missing invoice (see paragraph 2.3), cover solutions offered within the seller warranty (see paragraph 3.4.2). </span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">To increase the probability that the customer will keep the device, for all partial refunds or goodwill gestures, the amount will be rounded up to the nearest 5$. For example, a refund of 7$ will be rounded up to 10$. This does not apply to partial refunds for late express shipping, which will be refunded at the exact shipping cost.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">The minimum commercial gesture is 5 €/$/£.<br></span></p>\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"> </div>\n<div><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><u><strong>Below are information from the Quality Charter: </strong></u><br><br><strong>3.6.1 IN CASE OF LATE SHIPPING</strong><br>If your customer’s delivery is delayed by 1 or more days, whether due to delays on your part or a shipping provider’s, your customer is entitled to a refund equivalent to the shipping cost. <br></span></div>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"> <strong>3.5.5 If a refund failed for an order paid with PayPal</strong><br>Back Market will make a goodwill gesture at the seller’s expense in order to refund the customer and inform both the seller and the customer in the customer request discussion.<br><br>This is most of the time due to insufficient amounts on the PayPal account. In that case, a credit request is made at the seller’s expense and the refund should not be made via PayPal.<br><br><strong>2.3 What happens if you don’t provide the IMEI or serial number ? </strong><br>If a customer requests the IMEI or serial number at any time, you will have1 business day to provide it. If you haven’t provided the number after 24 hours, Back Market may offer your customer a goodwill gesture valued up to 50€/$/£ or an order cancellation.<br><br><strong>2.4 What happens if you don’t send an invoice ?</strong><br>If you don’t send the invoice within 2 business days following Back Market’s reminder, the customer is entitled to a free cancellation of their order or a goodwill gesture valued at up to €50/$50/£50.<br><br><strong>3.4.2 SELLER WARRANTY : SOLUTIONS TO OFFER</strong><br>You can offer return assistance and/or alternative solutions if appropriate or if your customer clearly asks for other options. This can include simple remote troubleshooting, offering a goodwill gesture in accordance with the Quality Charter requirements, or sending a new removable battery when it can be easily changed by your customer.</span><br><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"> </span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">This means: covering some repair costs with a goodwill gesture.</span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;\"> </p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>3.6.2 In case of missing or defective accessories </strong></span><br><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">In the event of a missing or defective standard accessory, the agent will offer your customer a choice between the following options:</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<ul><li style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">A goodwill gesture according to the amounts indicated in table below</span></li><li style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">The missing accessory</span></li></ul>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;\"> </p>\n<div align=\"left\">\n<div align=\"left\">\n<div align=\"left\">\n<table style=\"width: 99.0262%;border-color: #000000;border-style: solid;height: 1886.96px;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 29.8618%;\"></col><col style=\"width: 17.5337%;\"></col><col style=\"width: 17.5337%;\"></col><col style=\"width: 17.5337%;\"></col><col style=\"width: 17.5371%;\"></col></colgroup><tbody><tr style=\"height: 51.3021px;\"><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;text-align: center;\">\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Standard Accessories</strong></span></p>\n</td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;text-align: center;\"